# PART 2: ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

## 2.1 The 6 Layers — The Big Picture

```
                     INPUT MESSAGE
           "hi I want to return order #5678 🙏"
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 1: Emoji-Aware Tokeniser  │
            │  Split text into tokens + emojis  │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 2: BiLSTM-CRF Model       │
            │  Neural NER — label each token    │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 3: ILP Validator          │
            │  Enforce hard rules via OR-Tools  │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 4: MC Dropout             │
            │  Quantify uncertainty (T=10)      │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 5: Decision Engine        │
            │  Urgency + routing + action       │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
            ┌───────────────▼──────────────────┐
            │   LAYER 6: API Dispatcher         │
            │  Zendesk / Slack / PostgreSQL     │
            └───────────────┬──────────────────┘
                            │
                     STRUCTURED OUTPUT
```

## 2.2 The Tag Set (What the Model Learns)

The model uses **BIO tagging** to label every token:

| Tag | Meaning | Example |
|-----|---------|---------|
| `O` | Outside — not an entity | "hi", "want", "to" |
| `B-ORDER_ID` | Beginning of an Order ID | "#5678" |
| `I-ORDER_ID` | Inside (continuation) of an Order ID | (if order spans multiple tokens) |
| `B-FLIGHT_ID` | Beginning of a Flight ID | "UA4821" |
| `I-FLIGHT_ID` | Inside Flight ID | (rare) |
| `B-ISSUE_TYPE` | Beginning of Issue | "return" |
| `I-ISSUE_TYPE` | Inside Issue | "not delivered" → B + I |
| `B-EVENT` | Beginning of Event | "cancelled" |
| `I-EVENT` | Inside Event | "been cancelled" |
| `B-TIME` | Beginning of Time | "3 hours" |
| `I-TIME` | Inside Time | "3 hours" span |

**11 total tags** (9 entity tags + O + PAD).

