# PART 13: FILES AND WHAT EACH ONE DOES

```
messi/
├── config.py           ← ALL hyperparameters in one place
│                          (LR, batch size, paths, tag set, etc.)
├── preprocessing.py    ← Tokeniser + spaCy loading + embeddings
├── model.py            ← BiLSTM-CRF architecture (CharCNN, LSTM, CRF)
├── train.py            ← Training loop, optimiser, early stopping
├── evaluate.py         ← Token F1, span F1, Cohen's κ on test set
├── benchmark.py        ← Speed/latency tests, architecture stats
├── demo.py             ← CLI demo (12 showcase messages)
├── server.py           ← Flask web server + REST API
├── main.py             ← load_pipeline() and predict() — the interface
├── ilp.py              ← ILP constraint solver (OR-Tools)
├── uncertainty.py      ← MC Dropout + entropy + confidence
├── api.py              ← API dispatcher (Zendesk, Slack, etc.)
├── data_utils.py       ← Synthetic data generator
├── download_datasets.py ← HuggingFace dataset downloader
├── run_all.py          ← One command to run all 6 stages
│
├── data/
│   ├── annotated/
│   │   ├── train.jsonl (4,000 samples, 80%)
│   │   ├── val.jsonl   (500 samples, 10%)
│   │   └── test.jsonl  (500 samples, 10%)
│   └── emoji_vocab.json  (emoji → index mapping)
│
├── models/
│   ├── best_bilstm_crf.pt  ← Saved checkpoint (F1=0.56 on real data)
│   └── train_log.csv       ← Epoch-by-epoch training log
│
└── static/
    └── index.html      ← Web UI (glassmorphism dark theme)
```

